4: Get up, freak! Time for work!
7:
You should be GRATEFUL. You've got
special opponents today. Should be
more fun than monsters. Lucky you!
8:
Sounds like the lord himself is gonna
be watching, so you better put up a
DAMN GOOD FIGHT, got it?
10: KILL IT! KILL IT! KILL IT!
17:
Milord, you can't—
That's a man-eating beast!
19:
SILENCE! I came to speak with him,
not YOU. Leave us!
22:
So you're the Hellcat of the Dunes.
Nice to finally meet you!
29:
Ooh, you really can speak!
I had a hunch you could!
31:
Ah, I forgot to introduce myself.
I'm Rolan! The king appointed me
as lord of this domain.
36:
...Don't have one.
Just call me whatever.
39:
Okay! You're white and fluffy like
a cloud, so let's go with Nimbus!
46:
Hey, YOU'RE the one who said I could
call you whatever I want... Anyways,
I wanted to ask you something.
48: Why did you spare your opponents?
52:
Why? 'Cause I'm not gonna play along
with something like that.
58:
I wanted to see the scum up at the top
sweat. See 'em squirm in their seats.
That's all...
61:
Bahaha! What a sourpuss!
You've got a sharp tongue, huh?
63: Nimbus, how about you come with me?
65:
There are plenty of pompous fools
out there in need of reality checks!
What do you say? You don't belong
in a cage!
68:
Heh. Hahaha! Go play hero somewhere
else, kid.
70:
Doesn't make a difference whether
I'm in a cage here or some brat's
playroom... I'm not gonna be your
widdle kitty cat.
77:
Y'know, for a warrior that took down
three foes at once, you're a big
scaredy-cat.
85:
I said you don't belong in a cage!
Don't you wanna see the world?
Door's open—the rest is on you.
87:
What are you afraid of? You could lop
my head off with the flick of a paw
if you wanted. Come on out!
91:
Fine, you're on... But you better not
forget those words!
97:
...You're not getting away! Nimbus!
It went that way!
102:
Ooh, nice one, Nimbus! I'll trade you
for it! How's an IOU for thirty minutes
of grooming from yours truly sound?
106:
Brush your OWN hair. I'll keep my nice,
juicy salamander.
110:
Don't you have a meeting with the
borderland reps soon? You sure you've
got time to goof off here?
119: All right, all right, finish chewing first!
123:
...Gulp. I can't head out to a big
important meeting on an empty
stomach!
125:
It's plain as day who would win in a
fight, so I have to keep them from
butting heads with the crown!
129:
...Who would've thought the lord
himself was conspiring with rebels.
Imagine the looks on the other nobles'
faces if they knew.
132:
I'm not "conspiring." It's my JOB to keep
things here under control!
134:
Mark my words, Nimbus. Someday,
my dreams—OUR dreams—will come
true. We'll knock those jerks off their
high horses!
136:
And then, once I figure out where the
legendary village of stars is, we should
be able to find your hom—
139:
That old bedtime story of yours? Here
we go again... You read too many fairy
tales.
144: The village of stars is REAL!
161:
...Oh? Mmm?! I never would have
thought salamander tasted like this.
166: Same... It sure is spicy, but it's not bad.
175:
I was just remembering how I used to
make this back in the desert.
...All I really did was roast it, though.
178:
Cooking at high temperatures requires
considerable skill.
181:
So this is what you went off to the
desert for... Were you okay out there
on your own?
184:
Course I was. I can take care of myself.
Besides, despite everything, I have
plenty of good memories there too...
188: Ahh. This stuff really hits the spot...
